    {
      "id": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Agent memory and context management",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 27
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Agent memory, what is and is not collectable locally\n\n**Context window memory (collectable, real):** input tokens per turn, `max_prompt_tokens`, and the cache read/creation split above show how the agent fills and reuses its working context. Peak window % is your early warning before the model must drop or compact context.\n\n**Context compaction/summarization (collectable when triggered):** GitHub Copilot emits `copilot_chat.agent.summarization.count` when it summarizes context, and the CLI runtime emits compaction and truncation events with token deltas. These appear only after a long session forces compaction. The coverage dashboard tracks whether they have fired yet.\n\n**VS Code process memory (separate, OS level):** RSS of the VS Code/Electron processes is not part of GitHub Copilot OTel. It is sampled locally by `$HOME/frontier-cockpit/local-otel/sample-vscode-memory.sh` and shown in the VS Code Process Memory dashboard. That is operating system memory, not model context.\n\n**Chat memory files (project level):** the memory tool writes files under your repo or user profile. Those are inspected as files, not as OTel signals."
      }
    }
  ],
